        <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersG173"/>
        <p>A <a href="ch66s14.html#MonstersG172">gray render</a> attacks to kill, whether to bring down prey or to protect itself or those it has adopted. When hunting, it sometimes attempts to hide and wait for prey to wander close.</p>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1818241"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersG174"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Improved Grab (Ex):</strong></span> To use this ability, a <a href="ch66s14.html#MonstersG172">gray render</a> must hit with its bite attack. It can then attempt to start a grapple as a free action without provoking an attack of opportunity.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1818281"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersG175"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Rend (Ex):</strong></span> A <a href="ch66s14.html#MonstersG172">gray render</a> that wins a grapple check after a successful bite attack establishes a hold, latching onto the opponent's body and tearing the flesh. This attack automatically deals 2d6+9 points of damage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1818322"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersG176"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Skills:</strong></span> <a href="ch66s14.html#MonstersG172">Gray renders</a> have a +4 racial bonus on <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills294">Spot</a> checks due to their six keen eyes.</p>
